LEGISLATIVE BILL 892
Introduced by Hansen, 16.
Read first time January 08, 2026
Committee: Health and Human Services
1 A BILL FOR AN ACT relating to the Massage Therapy Practice Act; to amend
2 section 38-1716, Revised Statutes Cumulative Supplement, 2024; to
3 change requirements relating to licensure of massage therapy
4 establishments; and to repeal the original section.
5 Be it enacted by the people of the State of Nebraska,
-1-

LB892 LB892
2026 2026
1 Section 1. Section 38-1716, Revised Statutes Cumulative Supplement,
2 2024, is amended to read:
3 38-1716 No person shall operate or profess or attempt to operate a
4 massage therapy establishment unless such establishment is licensed by
5 the department under the Massage Therapy Practice Act. The department
6 shall not issue or renew a license for a massage therapy establishment
7 until all requirements of the act have been complied with. No person
8 shall engage in any of the practices of massage therapy in any location
9 or premises other than a licensed massage therapy establishment except as
10 specifically permitted by the board in the act.
11 Sec. 2. Original section 38-1716, Revised Statutes Cumulative
12 Supplement, 2024, is repealed.
